        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>3 Highbury Grove</placeName>
                    <date>15 September 1856</date>
                    <salute>My Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I regret to say that I cannot join your pleasant party tomorrow. The enemy has too secure a hold of me. I am a little better but I am not yet “an upright man”, and my medical adviser says if I will go I may reckon on a return of the Malady in full force &amp; so I am obliged to succumb. What makes it more annoying to me is that the position of writing is one of my most painful ones &amp; so I know you will excuse my being brief in my communication</p>
                  <p>Most truly yours | J. S. Bowerbank</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
